File: An IEC voting station. eNCA JOHANNESBURG - The voter registration weekend for local government elections will be held on 17 and 18 July. The July voter registration period will be your only chance of ensuring you get to cast your vote in the local government elections. The IEC says eligible South Africans should use the period to confirm if they still appear on the voter’s roll. #eNCA #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/7CPl2xQXui The July voter registration period will be the only chance of ensuring South Africans get to cast vote in the local government elections. READ: Date set for local government elections The IEC says eligible South Africans should use the period to confirm if they still appear on the voter's roll. Eligible voters can find out more about where, when and how to register on the IEC's website.